The paper deals with the problem of foreground extraction, which is a common task in computer vision and graphics. The paper proposes a new algorithm that uses multiple sources of expertise to produce a superior result. This involves developing new agents for matting, background probability estimation, and total variation minimization. The paper also evaluates the proposed method against state-of-the-art methods. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Other likely sub-categories include cs.GR (Graphics), cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
